OL,4,Cacceptance on ongoing basis
OL,6,FIt said witnesses had highlighted
OL,7,Fpublic transport and infrastructure
OL,8,Ffor motorists as areas where cash
OL,9,Facceptance has become less common.
OL,11,FCharities and consumers also told the
OL,12,Fcommittee that local government and
OL,13,Flocal government-funded services are
OL,14,Fincreasingly cashless.
OL,16,FIn January, economic secretary to the
OL,17,FTreasury Emma Reynolds told a Treasury
OL,18,FCommittee hearing that the Government
OL,19,Fhad "no plans" to regulate businesses
OL,20,Fto compel them to accept cash ` big or
OL,21,Fsmall.
